place.name: WINTHORPE
place.gazetteerText: WINTHORPE, a parish in Spilsby district, Lincoln; 5½ miles E by S of Gunby r. station, and 10¾ E of Spilsby. Post town, Burgh, under Boston. Acres, 2,339. Real property, £5,077. Pop., 305. Houses, 50. The manor belongs to Lord Monson. The living is a vicarage, annexed to Burgh. The church is good. Charities, £6. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
